title: Evaluating Health Inequities and Social Determinants in Delaware County, Ohio
author: Author A. B.
summary: This study investigates how social determinants of health—such as education, housing affordability, and access to care—affect health disparities in Delaware County, Ohio. Special focus is given to underserved populations and chronic condition prevalence.

statistical_analysis.findings: Residents in Delaware County, Ohio with low socioeconomic status experienced 1.7x greater rates of ER admissions and lower rates of preventive screening (p < 0.05). Areas with improved primary care access showed measurable improvement in health outcomes.

policy_implication: Recommendations for Delaware County, Ohio include expanding Medicaid, increasing local primary care availability, and strengthening educational outreach around chronic disease prevention.
references: Delaware County, Ohio Health Department Indicators Report

summary: This study investigates how social determinants of health—such as education, housing affordability, and access to care—affect health disparities in Wood County, Ohio. Special focus is given to underserved populations and chronic condition prevalence.

statistical_analysis.findings: Residents in Wood County, Ohio with low socioeconomic status experienced 1.7x greater rates of ER admissions and lower rates of preventive screening (p < 0.05). Areas with improved primary care access showed measurable improvement in health outcomes.

policy_implication: Recommendations for Wood County, Ohio include expanding Medicaid, increasing local primary care availability, and strengthening educational outreach around chronic disease prevention.
references: Wood County, Ohio Health Department Indicators Report
